|
:INFO
Ferment and Press
Ferment the full mash at 10 to 12 C (50 to 54 F) for 18 to 25 days, stirring gently once \
daily for the first week. The mash will foam actively then slowly calm. When activity \
slows and the liquid tastes clean and alcoholic, it is ready to press. Pour the

:QUOTE
Every master brewer will tell you that good sake is made in the cold. Heat is \
the enemy of clarity, both in the mash and in the mind of the brewer.
